value.name: Florida - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Florida is a state in the Southeastern region of the United States, bordered to the west by the Gulf of Mexico; Alabama to the northwest; Georgia to the north; the Bahamas and Atlantic Ocean to the east; and the Straits of Florida and Cuba to the south. value.name: Florida | Map, Population, History, & Facts | Britannica
value.snippet: Florida, constituent state of the United States of America. It was admitted as the 27th state in 1845. Florida is the most populous of the southeastern states and the second most populous Southern state after Texas. The capital is Tallahassee, located in the northwestern panhandle.

value.snippet: Florida er den sørligste av de 48 fastlandsdelstatene. Staten grenser til Georgia og Alabama i nord. Selv om Florida har en del kupert terreng, har den ingen høye fjelltopper.
